1
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:15,820
Fairy Tail...

2
00:00:16,390 --> 00:00:18,580
Natsu...san?

3
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:25,040
You came here to pick a fight with Master?

4
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:27,210
That's suicidal!

5
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,640
Fro thinks so, too...

6
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:04,930
Are you serious, kid?

7
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:09,320
Anybody who doesn't think of 
their comrades as comrades

8
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:11,100
is on my list!

9
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:13,730
Is he talking about Yukino?

10
00:02:14,210 --> 00:02:16,460
That's got nothin' to do with you!

11
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:19,450
Who would storm in here 
over something like that?!

12
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,550
I don't know what you're talking about,

13
00:02:22,550 --> 00:02:27,650
but I suppose you've got your reasons.

14
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:30,420
You don't know what I'm talkin' about?!

15
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:32,140
Dobengal.

16
00:02:32,140 --> 00:02:33,840
Deal with him.

17
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,790
Yes, sir!

18
00:02:35,450 --> 00:02:36,850
You're avoiding me?

19
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:41,280
A guild soldier like you needs 
100 more years of experience.

20
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:47,640
If you want a shot at the top, you'll have 
to prove yourself. Show me what you can do.

21
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,070
Pandemonium!

22
00:02:53,610 --> 00:02:56,080
Fight me!

23
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:58,280
You're not getting near the master!

24
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:10,880
I, Dobengal, am not taking 
part in the Grand Magic Games,

25
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:15,290
but when it comes to skill, I'm just as 
strong as any of the participants here.

26
00:03:15,650 --> 00:03:18,590
I'm going to show you 
the power of Sabertooth!

27
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,510
A smokescreen, huh?

28
00:03:27,890 --> 00:03:29,700
You don't know who you're messing with.

29
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,520
You should withdraw immediately.

30
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,510
Get out!

31
00:03:32,940 --> 00:03:34,910
Outta my way!

32
00:03:35,350 --> 00:03:37,280
My beef ain't with you!

33
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,640
I don't believe it...

34
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,580
Dobengal's down?!

35
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,500
He's one of the top ten strongest 
wizards in our guild!

36
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:51,640
Master, let me...

37
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,330
Don't do a thing.

38
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:57,130
Kid, there aren't any like you in my guild.

39
00:03:57,580 --> 00:03:59,380
Amusing.

40
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:07,680
Is that all...

41
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,100
...you've got?!

42
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,460
Firing Hammer...

43
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:41,910
...of the Lightning Flame Dragon!

44
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:01,400
Minerva!

45
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:03,340
My lady!

46
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:13,010
Shall we end this evening's 
entertainment here?

47
00:05:14,540 --> 00:05:18,700
Minerva, I didn't ask you to step in...

48
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:20,010
Of course,

49
00:05:20,010 --> 00:05:24,070
if this had continued, you 
would have won, Father.

50
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,130
Father?

51
00:05:26,370 --> 00:05:30,960
However, the world cares about appearances.

52
00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:34,320
Even though this one came 
here and attacked you,

53
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:40,400
if the master of Sabertooth annihilated 
a participant in the Grand Magic Games,

54
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:43,020
it would cause difficulty for all of us.

55
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:47,360
I'll tell ya one thing... if anybody's 
gettin' wiped out, it's him!

56
00:05:47,650 --> 00:05:50,080
My father has somewhat warmed to this battle,

57
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:54,190
but cannot back down in 
front of his subordinates.

58
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,800
What do you think?

59
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:59,050
Will you allow us to save face?

60
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:08,620
If you do, I'll return this 
kitten to you unharmed.

61
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:11,340
Happy!

62
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:15,320
I'm sorry, Natsu!

63
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:17,180
Dammit!

64
00:06:17,550 --> 00:06:20,280
You've incapacitated several of our people,

65
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:24,950
but we're willing to overlook this incident.

66
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:29,570
In exchange, I'm asking you 
to behave in a mature fashion.

67
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:39,660
Natsu!

68
00:06:39,660 --> 00:06:43,220
I'm sorry! They caught me at the entrance!

69
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:44,630
It's okay, Happy.

70
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,880
It's my fault for leaving you behind.

71
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,340
Natsu!

72
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:52,350
Let's go.

73
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:53,470
Aye!

74
00:06:56,260 --> 00:06:59,290
That kid's got grit.

75
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:02,440
We'll settle this at the Grand Magic Games.

76
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,270
To our hearts' content.

77
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:09,090
We ain't gonna lose to the likes of you.

78
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:12,490
In fact, you won't be 
able to keep up with us.

79
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:21,090
If you call yourself a guild, 
take care of your comrades.

80
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:24,230
That's all I wanted to say.

81
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,960
Comrades...

82
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:35,820
We don't have that kind of bond in our guild.

83
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:40,610
Y-You're that strong,

84
00:07:40,610 --> 00:07:42,770
Natsu Dragneel?!

85
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,650
Hey! I'm gonna compete tomorrow!

86
00:07:45,690 --> 00:07:49,070
I can't just let him get 
away with this carnage!

87
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:52,090
You mean you're going to unleash the 
power of Black Lightning, right?

88
00:07:52,090 --> 00:07:55,980
Certainly, this was rather one-sided carnage,

89
00:07:57,050 --> 00:08:01,250
but without something like this, 
we would've lost our spark.

90
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:04,120
Anyway, we need someone to replace Yukino.

91
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:07,520
I think I'll get in on the fun.

92
00:08:12,020 --> 00:08:14,470
You fought Sabertooth?!

93
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:17,980
Actually, I wanted to mix 
it up with 'em even more...

94
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:20,810
Too bad it ended right as 
I was gettin' fired up.

95
00:08:20,810 --> 00:08:22,820
I'm sorry, Natsu!

96
00:08:22,820 --> 00:08:25,350
It's my fault, for getting caught!

97
00:08:25,590 --> 00:08:29,140
What are you talking about?! We're 
lucky it ended the way it did!

98
00:08:29,140 --> 00:08:30,770
That's right!

99
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:33,650
If one of their team 
members had been injured,

100
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:36,330
we might've been disqualified!

101
00:08:37,210 --> 00:08:41,290
Come to think of it, that Minerva 
chick was sayin' something like that.

102
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:44,080
<i>You</i> are incredibly stupid!

103
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:46,230
Use your head a little!

104
00:08:46,230 --> 00:08:47,730
Exactly!

105
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:50,490
Pour it on, Gray! Read him the riot act!

106
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:54,600
If you were gonna take the fight 
to them, you should've invited me!

107
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,600
It's not fair, you getting 
to have all the fun!

108
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,470
You're missing the point!

109
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:03,970
Just because you're frustrated 
from losing a match,

110
00:09:03,970 --> 00:09:06,940
there's nothing admirable about getting 
payback in a fight outside the arena.

111
00:09:06,940 --> 00:09:09,210
That's not what it's about!

112
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:13,260
I just wanted to deliver a 
message to that Rufus bastard...

113
00:09:13,610 --> 00:09:15,450
"I'm not gonna lose next time!"

114
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,430
Anyway, I'm not lettin' 
those jerks off the hook.

115
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:22,830
A comrade's someone who's got 
your back and you got theirs...

116
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,720
Being strict is one thing,

117
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:30,880
but humiliating a girl and then kicking 
her out, that's as low as you can go!

118
00:09:31,590 --> 00:09:33,290
That Yukino girl,

119
00:09:33,290 --> 00:09:37,630
even after being abused like 
that, she came to see me...

120
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,700
I wonder where she is now...

121
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,260
I'm worried.

122
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:45,550
She did say she has nowhere to go...

123
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:50,760
Dammit! I'm still seething!

124
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,320
I think I'll go back there 
an' fight some more!

125
00:09:52,570 --> 00:09:54,220
Alright! Count me in!

126
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:56,230
You can't do that!

127
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:59,500
Can't you just settle it at the tournament?!

128
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:02,500
Although now that you've riled up Sabertooth,

129
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:06,000
from tomorrow on, they'll probably 
go even harder on us in the matches!

130
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:12,620
It doesn't matter which guild they're in,

131
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:16,920
all wizards have their own feelings.

132
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:27,750
Move it!

133
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:28,980
Let us go!

134
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:30,630
Stop it, I said!

135
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,130
Listen, you two...

136
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:42,400
Would you cut it out?!

137
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,610
Yes, ma'am!

138
00:10:52,140 --> 00:10:53,540
Hey, did you hear?

139
00:10:53,540 --> 00:10:54,950
About last night, right?!

140
00:10:54,950 --> 00:10:55,920
What are you talking about?

141
00:10:55,920 --> 00:11:00,940
Apparently, somebody 
attacked Sabertooth's inn!

142
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:05,110
What kind of fool would 
pick a fight with Saber?!

143
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:07,730
Beats me!

144
00:11:07,730 --> 00:11:10,810
Well, brawls happen outside 
the arena every year, right?

145
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:13,510
This is a festival, so they 
should take it public!

146
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,590
Natsu-sama...?

147
00:11:20,450 --> 00:11:26,030
A guild that makes its family 
members cry ain't no guild at all!

148
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:31,370
Don't tell me he did it for...

149
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:42,410
We're at the halfway point 
in the Grand Magic Games.

150
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:44,180
The beginning of the third day!

151
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:48,310
I wonder what kind of passionate 
dramas we'll see today?

152
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,250
Our guest today

153
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:54,460
is Lahar-san, from the Magic Council.

154
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:56,310
It's been a long time, hasn't it?

155
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,070
Thank you for this opportunity.

156
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:03,370
Lahar-san, you're the Captain of the 
Enforcement and Detention Corps...

157
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,490
Yes.

158
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:08,160
I won't stand for any shenanigans 
during the tournament.

159
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,320
That's the captain for you.

160
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:15,690
He never forgets his duties.

161
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:17,910
Damn you, Lahar...

162
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:19,900
Why'd you make me come here?

163
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:26,240
A guest of the Grand Magic Games?!

164
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:27,850
You?

165
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:30,310
I have no reason to decline.

166
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:32,890
Come with me, Doranbolt.

167
00:12:32,890 --> 00:12:34,850
No, I...

168
00:12:35,610 --> 00:12:38,410
You want to see Fairy Tail 
alive and well, don't you?

169
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:40,910
Don't you wonder about them?

170
00:12:41,290 --> 00:12:43,270
How could I not?

171
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,660
Still, the way I am now...

172
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:49,170
Are you still hung up on what 
happened seven years ago?

173
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:52,310
About what you perceive of 
as abandoning Fairy Tail?

174
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:57,020
They're looking forward.

175
00:12:57,460 --> 00:13:01,130
The only one who's dragged 
down by the past is you.

176
00:13:08,050 --> 00:13:10,620
Oh, no! The match is starting!

177
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:13,740
It's your fault! You just had to get 
a fish-kebab from that food stand!

178
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:16,740
It smelled so good, I couldn't help myself!

179
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:18,440
Whatever, let's just hurry!

180
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:24,900
I'm going to announce the competition 
for this, the third day of the Games!

181
00:13:25,070 --> 00:13:26,750
The name of the event...

182
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:28,780
...is Pandemonium!

183
00:13:29,030 --> 00:13:31,480
What does "pandemonium" mean?

184
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:33,500
It's an abode of demons.

185
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:37,290
Like a building where lots of demons lurk...

186
00:13:37,290 --> 00:13:40,660
I wonder if they're doing a haunted house...

187
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:43,800
They're walking down a 
dark path and suddenly...

188
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:47,260
...something like this jumps out!

189
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:50,820
I don't think I like "pandemonium"...

190
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:53,560
I-I'm scared, too!

191
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:56,930
Even though you're a ghost yourself?!

192
00:13:57,320 --> 00:14:00,440
There will be one participant 
from each guild.

193
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,570
Please choose your representative!

194
00:14:02,570 --> 00:14:04,160
I'll do it!

195
00:14:04,450 --> 00:14:07,240
I gotta continue what I started last night!

196
00:14:07,290 --> 00:14:09,600
You don't get to decide all by yourself!

197
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:13,130
If it's a revenge match, I wanna do it, too!

198
00:14:13,190 --> 00:14:16,020
No. I'll go.

199
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:20,170
You going out there may only 
make things more complicated.

200
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:23,420
I agree! Good luck, Erza!

201
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:24,840
Fight!

202
00:14:24,850 --> 00:14:26,780
Let me do it!

203
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,130
Would you calm down?!

204
00:14:29,130 --> 00:14:31,770
I'll participate for B Team.

205
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:33,160
Wait a second!

206
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:35,670
It's about time that I get to do something!

207
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:39,170
Cana, how could you go, when 
you're a reserve member?

208
00:14:39,170 --> 00:14:41,000
What happened to Mystogan?

209
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,560
Juvia hasn't seen him yet today...

210
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:46,450
With the guest commentator 
being a member of the Council,

211
00:14:46,450 --> 00:14:48,310
I should be able to participate, right?

212
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,280
That's true...

213
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:54,490
If Er-chan is gonna do this, 
let me go too, Kagura-chan!

214
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:56,070
I'll allow it.

215
00:14:58,380 --> 00:15:00,240
I'm not gonna lose, Er-chan!

216
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,040
Right!

217
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:04,080
I hate Jellal, too...

218
00:15:04,850 --> 00:15:06,760
He used us...

219
00:15:07,230 --> 00:15:09,350
...and murdered Simon.

220
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:10,530
I'll never forgive him...

221
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:12,880
I'll never forgive him!

222
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:18,020
I have to focus!

223
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:21,620
From Mermaid Heel, it looks like 
Millianna is taking the field!

224
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,580
That girl!

225
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:24,850
Millianna...

226
00:15:24,850 --> 00:15:28,650
She's the one who was wearing the hood. 
I didn't know she was in a guild.

227
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:34,100
Don't cause trouble in 
front of the Council, Obra.

228
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:38,130
I'll be the rep for Pegasus.

229
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:42,140
Like I said last night, I'm 
participating in this one.

230
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:45,580
I'll use my Black Lightning to 
blast them all to smithereens.

231
00:15:45,850 --> 00:15:49,820
Even though we don't know what kind 
of competition it's going to be?

232
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:53,380
Do what you want.

233
00:15:53,580 --> 00:15:57,220
If Natsu Dragneel isn't gonna be 
in it, I don't care what happens.

234
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,170
Jura-san is going to do it?

235
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:04,840
On Obaba's orders, so we 
can't do anything about it.

236
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,400
My sock...

237
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,590
Just buy a new one!

238
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:10,980
Count on me.

239
00:16:11,340 --> 00:16:13,180
All of the participants have been selected!

240
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:15,300
From Sabertooth, Orga!

241
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:17,200
From Lamia Scale, Jura!

242
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:19,630
From Blue Pegasus, Hibiki!

243
00:16:19,630 --> 00:16:21,620
From Raven Tail, Obra!

244
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:24,150
From Mermaid Heel, Millianna!

245
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,440
From Quatro Puppy, Novali!

246
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:28,750
From Fairy Tail A, Erza!

247
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:30,850
From Fairy Tail B, Cana!

248
00:16:30,850 --> 00:16:33,300
These are our eight competitors!

249
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,200
What is that?!

250
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,320
Wow...

251
00:16:56,830 --> 00:16:58,620
Begin analysis.

252
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:14,970
Pandemonium, a temple 
haunted by evil monsters!

253
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:16,610
It's huge!

254
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:20,050
Haunted by monsters, he says?

255
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:22,960
That's the idea-kabo.

256
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:27,490
There are 100 monsters inside this temple.

257
00:17:27,490 --> 00:17:30,930
That being said, they're actually 
magical manifestations that we created,

258
00:17:30,930 --> 00:17:34,400
so everyone can relax. There's 
no danger of you being attacked.

259
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:38,410
The monsters are D, C, B, A, S!

260
00:17:38,410 --> 00:17:41,520
Those are the five levels of battle 
power the monsters are divided into.

261
00:17:41,650 --> 00:17:44,370
This is how it breaks down.

262
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,130
Incidentally...

263
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:50,790
...if you're curious about just how 
strong the D-class monsters are...

264
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:09,430
Ones like these

265
00:18:09,430 --> 00:18:12,960
and ones even stronger, 100 of them 
wandering around the temple...

266
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:15,600
That's Pandemonium-kabo!

267
00:18:17,510 --> 00:18:20,110
Even though he says they're 
just magical manifestations,

268
00:18:20,110 --> 00:18:22,930
if you get attacked by them, 
you're hurt for real, right?

269
00:18:22,930 --> 00:18:25,560
Will Erza and Cana be okay?

270
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:28,580
I'd like to think that those 
two will be alright, but...

271
00:18:29,190 --> 00:18:31,680
This is a really extravagant 
competition, don't you think?

272
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:34,340
Though it feels like they may 
be going a little too far...

273
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:41,080
Please note that as the class 
of the monsters goes up,

274
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:44,280
their fighting strength 
increases exponentially.

275
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:47,400
The S-class monster is so strong 
that there's no guarantee

276
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:51,060
even one of the 10 Great Wizard 
Saints can defeat it-kabo.

277
00:18:53,310 --> 00:18:58,520
In order, each of you will choose 
the number of monsters to battle.

278
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:01,050
It's called your "right to challenge".

279
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:02,240
Right to challenge?

280
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:05,690
For example, if you choose three monsters,

281
00:19:05,690 --> 00:19:09,360
three of them will appear inside the temple.

282
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:12,920
The person who chooses them 
enters the temple alone.

283
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:18,500
If the player successfully destroys 
them, he or she gets three points.

284
00:19:18,950 --> 00:19:24,540
The next player then has the right to 
challenge up to 97 of the remaining monsters.

285
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:27,220
And so on and so on,

286
00:19:27,650 --> 00:19:30,110
until there are zero monsters left!

287
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:35,190
Alternatively, if everyone runs out of magic 
power, the game is over at that point.

288
00:19:35,810 --> 00:19:37,860
It's like a counting game.

289
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:39,390
That's right!

290
00:19:39,390 --> 00:19:43,290
Assessing the situation when your 
turn comes around becomes important!

291
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:45,830
However, as I mentioned before,

292
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:48,460
the monsters are ranked.

293
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:52,160
Whether the player uses their 
right to challenge one or five,

294
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:55,840
the monsters appear randomly.

295
00:19:56,340 --> 00:20:02,190
In other words, you need a strategy to avoid 
running into the S-class monster, right?

296
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:07,470
If it's random, having a strategy 
like that won't do you any good.

297
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:12,810
Not true. Between probability 
theory and my Archive,

298
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,440
strategy will work to some extent.

299
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:18,320
Irrespective of the monster's rank,

300
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:22,140
you'll get one point for 
each monster you destroy.

301
00:20:22,140 --> 00:20:27,660
Once you enter the temple, you 
can't exit until you've succeeded.

302
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:31,180
What happens if we go down 
while inside the temple?

303
00:20:31,650 --> 00:20:35,660
The number of points you've earned 
during your turn stays as is,

304
00:20:35,660 --> 00:20:40,590
but the number of destroys you've had 
that turn goes to zero, and you're out.

305
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:44,840
Then it's bad to get too greedy.

306
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:49,320
But if you only go with one monster per 
turn, you'll fall behind the others.

307
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:54,060
And you also have to consider how much magic 
you'll recover before it's your next turn.

308
00:20:54,230 --> 00:20:56,730
This is surprisingly difficult, huh?

309
00:20:57,210 --> 00:21:00,010
Well, let's see what happens...

310
00:21:00,470 --> 00:21:02,710
...with the two from our guild.

311
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:06,060
Alright, let's decide on the order.

312
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:07,620
Please draw your lots.

313
00:21:11,580 --> 00:21:12,580
Number one!

314
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:18,150
You're lucky! It'll go back around 
to being your turn the most.

315
00:21:18,150 --> 00:21:20,590
I got number eight...

316
00:21:21,570 --> 00:21:23,010
With this competition,

317
00:21:23,260 --> 00:21:26,970
I thought winning or losing all 
depended on the luck of the draw...

318
00:21:27,290 --> 00:21:30,580
Luck of the draw? I don't know about that...

319
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:32,100
More than the order of battle,

320
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:36,380
pacing yourself and situational 
judgment are important in this game.

321
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:37,440
No.

322
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:40,160
This isn't a game anymore.

323
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:51,240
All 100 will be my opponents!

324
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:53,410
I exercise my right to challenge...

325
00:21:54,890 --> 00:21:56,060
...100!

326
00:23:55,690 --> 00:23:58,910
100 monsters all by herself, 
she says! Erza really is scary!

327
00:23:58,910 --> 00:24:01,810
It's like Erza is the one who's the monster!

328
00:24:01,810 --> 00:24:03,540
Does she actually have all that armor?!

329
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:06,420
Heaven's Wheel Armor, Black Wing, 
Flame Empress, Sea Empress,

330
00:24:06,420 --> 00:24:08,860
Flight, Adamantine, Giant, 
Lightning Empress...

331
00:24:08,860 --> 00:24:12,170
I bet she has, like, Red Ogre 
Armor and Hag Armor, too!

332
00:24:12,170 --> 00:24:14,010
She's gonna get mad at you again!

333
00:24:14,210 --> 00:24:16,550
Next time: 100 to 1!

334
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:20,250
But really, this is supposed to 
be a team competition, right?

335
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,490
Ah, this is fine.

336
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:22,890
After all, it's Erza!

